MCQ-

The correct syntax for creating composite indexes in MS SQL Sever is:

1) CREATE INDEX index_name ON table_name(column1), table_name(column2);
2) CREATE INDEX index_name ON table_name(column1) and table_name(column2);
3) CREATE INDEX index_name ON table_name(column1, column2);
4) All the above-mentioned syntax are correct.

Correct Ans- CREATE INDEX index_name ON table_name(column1, column2);

Explanation-
A composite index is an index on two or more columns of a table. 
Syntax
CREATE INDEX index_name
on table_name (column1, column2);
